# .dockerignore for the commit-image build.
# Goal: bake in the FULL repo (including .git history — the grader uses it),
# dropping only local build artifacts and editor/OS cruft. Dev image, not minimal.
# Lands at the fork root (the build context) when the template is copied in.

# ── Build outputs / local cruft ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Keep build artifacts out of the context — the COPY boundary is what separates
# source from artifacts. build.sh produces its outputs under /mayhem at build time.
# Adjust the patterns per project.
build/
out/
*.o
*.a
*.so
*.dylib
**/__pycache__/
# M*LIB test suite build artifacts (tests/ produces these; build.sh rebuilds them in-image)
*.exe
tests/*.log
tests/*.log.err
tests/depend

# ── Editor / OS noise ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
